{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00947/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00947"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:09:47"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["dirty single"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man stares at a woman a she speaks to him."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00947","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00947"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1/22809cd6-d60f-47eb-b3ee-42bbaad247e3","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:21:10.707Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>It will become clear later that Reynolds’s depression after completing a major project is part of a pattern: the high of aesthetic bliss is followed by a crash that brings unpleasant memories and emotions to the tailor.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:32.108345534407015,67.79648609077609,215.12811127379211,140.68814055636895"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1/36939e14-b2c6-4f39-93ab-3f5da4ea6eb0","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:21:22.140Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds tells Cyril he has been having an unexplained, unsettled feeling, which he likens to butterflies. The sensation of butterflies is often associated with nervousness about a new love, like the one he will soon find in Alma. The line drawn between love and discomfort speaks to his dynamic with Alma throughout the film—a relationship that is both poisonous and regenerating.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00947/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:860.5234260614934,128.98243045388006,599.099560761347,688.4516837481698"}}}]}]}]}